title: Captain Marvel: Directors’ commentary
body:
Anna Boden and Ryan Fleck said that Goose is played mainly by Reggie (but also other cats) in Captain Marvel. And that Goose is female but she is played by a male because they were told by trainers that female cats are too difficult to train.

Boden suggests this is deeply embedded sexism in the animal trainer world. And I know nothing about cats (except that I imagine all of them are difficult to train), is there a reason why female cats would be more difficult?

Animal Tumblr, help a flerken fan.
